---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Refund Policy"
  description="Sound Buddy's refund policy — a 30-day full refund, no questions asked. Clear terms for monthly and annual subscribers."
  updated="July 7, 2026"
>
  <p>
    We want Sound Buddy to earn its place at your desk. If it doesn't, we'll refund you.
    This policy explains how refunds work for the Sound Buddy Pro subscription.
  </p>

  <div class="callout">
    <p><strong>30-day money-back guarantee.</strong> If you're not happy with Sound Buddy Pro
    for any reason within 30 days of your first payment, email us and we'll refund you in full —
    no questions asked.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Annual subscriptions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Within 30 days</strong> of your first payment — full refund, no questions asked.</li>
    <li><strong>Within 60 days</strong> — a prorated refund for the unused remainder of your year.</li>
    <li>After 60 days — the subscription runs to the end of your paid year and does not auto-refund,
      but you can cancel anytime to stop the next renewal.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Monthly subscriptions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Cancel anytime — you won't be charged again after you cancel.</li>
    <li>The current month is non-refundable, but your Pro access continues until the end of the
      period you've already paid for.</li>
    <li>Inside the first 30 days, the money-back guarantee above still applies.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to request a refund</h2>
  <p>
    Email <a href="mailto:support@soundbuddy.online">support@soundbuddy.online</a> from the address
    you purchased with. You'll get an automatic reply with next steps, and a person will follow up.
    Approved refunds are issued to your original payment method by Stripe, our payment processor,
    and typically appear within 5–10 business days depending on your bank.
  </p>

  <h2>Cancelling</h2>
  <p>
    Cancelling stops future charges and is separate from a refund. When your paid period ends, your
    license reverts to the free tier — your app, your recordings, and your report cards stay on your
    Mac. Nothing is deleted.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
